  "body": "As a frequent user of `kubectl explain` I propose we ignore the trailing period (`.`) character in the argument passed to this command:\r\n\r\n* As long as argument is non-empty when trailing period is removed, I think it's safe\r\n* You use `kubectl explain` by keep adding fields (e.g. `service`, then `service.spec`,  then `service.spec.ports` ...) so it's very easy to forget a trailing `.` at the end.\r\n* When a user leaves the `.` at the end, kubectl gives a super weird cryptic error (see below)\r\n\r\n```sh\r\n$ kubectl explain  ingress.spec.rules.http.paths.\r\nerror: field \"\" does not exist\r\n```\r\n\r\nI believe ignoring the trailing period(s) will be more forgiving and increase user success with `kubectl explain`. \r\n@jbeda might have something to add.\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n/sig cli\r\n",
